0+v1.9.2''></a><a class=''shareaholic-tweetbutton'' data-shr_count=''horizontal'' data-shr_href=''http%3A%2F%2Fajaydsouza.com%2Farchives%2F2012%2F12%2F29%2Ftop-10-v1-9-2%2F'' data-shr_title=''Top+10+v1.9.2''></a></div><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><div class="KonaBody"><p>I updated the <a href="http://ajaydsouza.com/wordpress/plugins/top-10/">Top 10</a> to v1.9.2 today and you can upgrade to the latest version of the plugin from within your WordPress Dashboard &gt; Updates.</p>\n<p>New in 1.9.2:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: Top 10 now has its own menu in the administration area. Access settings and view your top posts directly under the new menu: &#8220;Top 10&#8243;</li>\n<li>Added: New classes <strong>tptn_counter</strong> and <strong>tptn_list_count</strong> to style the displayed count</li>\n<li>Added: New option &#8220;Always display latest count for the post&#8221; to not use JavaScript to display the counts for a post. This speeds up since no external JS file is used to display the count. Ideal for those not using caching plugins or are not particularly worried if the counts are slightly older.</li>\n<li>Fixed: PHP notices when WP_DEBUG is turned on</li>\n<li>Modified: Updated timthumb.php</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you have any bugs to report or have any support questions, please post in the <a href="https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/top-10">Support Forums</a>. The comments section below is to tell me how much you love the plugin <img src=''http://i2.wp.com/ajaydsouza.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' data-recalc-dims="1" /> </p>\n<p>And, if you really love it, do <a href="http://wordpress.org/support/view/plugin-reviews/top-10">post a review</a>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div><div class="shr-publisher-2600"></div><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --